The man was transported to a nearby hospital in a stable condition. CAPE TOWN - A surfer has survived a shark attack in Port Alfred in the Eastern Cape on Wednesday. The incident happened at East Beach and the man was transported to a nearby hospital in a stable condition. The National Sea Rescue Institute’s Craig Lambinon said the beach had been closed until further notice. “The shark bit the surfer on the leg. It appeared to be a juvenile white shark. We urge caution to bathers in the Port Alfred area.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)